1. ID in Web Development
An ID is a unique identifier assigned to a single HTML element. It is used when you need to style or manipulate one specific element.

Syntax (HTML)
html
Copy
Edit
<div id="uniqueElement">This is a unique div</div>
CSS Example
css
Copy
Edit
#uniqueElement {
    color: red;
    font-size: 20px;
}
ðŸ’¡ Key Points:

IDs must be unique within a page.

Used when you want to target a single element specifically.

In CSS, IDs are selected using # (hash symbol).

In JavaScript, you can access an element by document.getElementById("uniqueElement").

2. Class in Web Development
A Class is used to style or manipulate multiple elements that share the same characteristics.

Syntax (HTML)
html
Copy
Edit
<div class="commonStyle">This is a styled div</div>
<p class="commonStyle">This is a styled paragraph</p>
CSS Example
css
Copy
Edit
.commonStyle {
    color: blue;
    font-size: 18px;
}
ðŸ’¡ Key Points:

Classes can be used multiple times on different elements.

In CSS, classes are selected using . (dot symbol).

In JavaScript, you can access multiple elements using document.getElementsByClassName("commonStyle").